Fruits and Their Water Needs
Apple

Water Need: Moderate (1-2 inches of water per week, especially during the growing season)
Banana

Water Need: High (1-2 inches of water per week, ensure consistent moisture)
Orange

Water Need: Moderate to High (1-2 inches of water per week, more during dry periods)
Grape

Water Need: Moderate (1 inch of water per week, more during dry spells)
Strawberry

Water Need: Moderate to High (1-1.5 inches of water per week, consistent moisture is crucial)
Pineapple

Water Need: Moderate (1 inch of water per week, less frequent in cooler weather)
Kiwi

Water Need: High (1-2 inches of water per week, consistent moisture is important)
Peach

Water Need: Moderate to High (1-1.5 inches of water per week, especially during fruit development)
Plum

Water Need: Moderate (1-1.5 inches of water per week, more during dry periods)
Cherry

Water Need: Moderate (1-1.5 inches of water per week, adjust for rainfall and temperature)
Mango

Water Need: Moderate (1-2 inches of water per week, reduce during cooler months)
Vegetables and Their Water Needs
Carrot

Water Need: Moderate (1 inch of water per week, keep soil consistently moist)
Tomato

Water Need: High (1-2 inches of water per week, consistent moisture is key)
Bell Pepper

Water Need: Moderate to High (1-1.5 inches of water per week, more during hot weather)
Cucumber

Water Need: High (1-2 inches of water per week, consistent moisture is crucial)
Lettuce

Water Need: High (1-1.5 inches of water per week, more in hot weather)
Spinach

Water Need: High (1-1.5 inches of water per week, consistent moisture is important)
Broccoli

Water Need: Moderate to High (1-1.5 inches of water per week, more in dry conditions)
Cauliflower

Water Need: High (1-1.5 inches of water per week, keep soil moist)
Zucchini

Water Need: High (1-2 inches of water per week, consistent moisture is important)
Beet

Water Need: Moderate (1 inch of water per week, keep soil evenly moist)